jobDescription.text:
Job Title: Forklift Driver

Company Location: Preferred location Indianapolis, IN, USA.

Roles and Responsibilities:
- Operate forklifts to move, load, and unload materials in a safe and efficient manner
- Follow company policies and procedures for material handling and movement
- Use dispatching systems to prioritize and fulfill orders
- Conduct routine inspections of forklifts and handling equipment to ensure proper functioning
- Complete paperwork and computer-based tasks related to material movement and inventory management
- Utilize RF scanner technology to track materials and inventory
- Maintain a clean and organized work area

Preferred Skills:
- Experience operating a forklift
- Knowledge of dispatching and material handling procedures
- Familiarity with handling equipment such as pallet jacks and hand trucks
- Basic computer skills including data entry and inventory management
- Ability to complete paperwork accurately and efficiently
- Proficiency in using RF scanner technology

Experience Level: Preferred experience level is 0 to 50 years.

Company Description: CoArtha, a Product Development company providing HR Technology Solutions to Enterprises using Machine Learning & Automation. CoArtha recognized as Top 10 HR Technology companies for 2017. (Source: Silicon India Magazine) and FINALIST into 2017 RED HERRING Asia Top 100. Our Enterprise customers are Randstad USA, Monster.com since 2015. We have 3 core areas of expertise to fulfill Enterprise's Talent Acquisition & Digital Transformation needs. • Product (https://www.MapRecruit.com - Parallel Automated Interview Screening to scale Talent Acquisition 10x at 30% of effort) • Intellectual Property (Candidate Match & Rank to Job, Parsing for 3 major domains - IT, Professional Services, Healthcare) • Solutions (HR Automation and Machine Learning -- User Modeling, Resume Enrichment, Deduplication, Visualization

At our company, we are committed to excellence in everything we do. As a Forklift Driver, you will play a crucial role in ensuring our materials are moved safely and efficiently. We value collaboration and teamwork, and we believe that every member of our team plays an important role in our success. If you are looking for a challenging and rewarding opportunity to work with a team of dedicated professionals, we invite you to apply for this position.
